name: TanDo - Style
description:
If you want the output more stylized like the artist, I recommend using a weight above 1.0, like up to 1.5. You should use hires fix.

LoRA trained with images from artist TanDo (https://www.pixiv.net/en/users/5899771), follow and support the artist!

This is a complete revamp of the first LoRA I posted. It is completely revamped and it is able to achieve great results! See for yourself the example images.

Trained on NAI and should work with most anime models.

Hope you enjoy! Please rate and give your feedback!

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

modelVersions.name: v1.0
modelVersions.description:
Trained using AbyssOrangeMix2 model

23 images, handpicked, not cropped, added .txt captions (WD1.4)

10 repeats, 20 epochs, batch size 2

LR: 0.001, Unet LR: 0.001, Text encoder LR: 0.0005

Net dim: 8, Net alpha: 8

Runtime ~15min
